  "summary": "H021 enabled only the missing vendor-observed MSI-lite/IOMMU fabric subset before the forced one-descriptor CMD18. The writes landed and persisted through the stall, but IDMAC still did not consume descriptor word 0: descriptor checksum/stamps were unchanged, OWN remained set, CHDA stayed at DLBA, CBDA stayed zero, and IDST stayed 0x4000. This closes the safe MSI/IOMMU subset as a standalone fix and argues against broadening to display/GMAC/VPU fabric bits without new source evidence."
